HEADWORD: Statal
<hw>Sta"tal</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"t⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or existing with reference to, a State of the American
Union, as distinguished from the general government.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have no knowledge of any other kind of political citizenship,
higher or lower, <qex>statal</qex> or national.</q> <rj><qau>Edward
Bates.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Statant</ent>⟦br⟧
